  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2, android.view.KeyEvent.Callback, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory, android.view.LayoutInflater.Factory2, android.view.View.OnCreateContextMenuListener, android.view.Window.Callback, android.view.Window.OnWindowDismissedCallback

    public class ProtocolSearch
extends android.app.Activity
    As mandated by SAE J1978 ยง7.1, this class provides the following functionality:
    • Provides an "Automatic hands-off determination of the communication protocol"
    • Informs the user that bus initialization is occurring
    • Prevent user intervention while each individual protocol test is occurring
    • Upon failure, advise the user of the following:
      1. That communication with the vehicle could not be established
      2. To confirm that the ignition key is in the "ON" position
      3. To check the emissions label or vehicle service information to confirm that the vehicle is OBD equipped and compliant
      4. To confirm that the external test equipment is connected to the vehicle correctly
    • Notifies the user of the number of failed initialization attempts
    • Retries the initialization process until succeeding or the user cancels

      • onBackPressed

        public final void onBackPressed()
        Called when the activity has detected the user's press of the back key. The default implementation simply finishes the current activity, but you can override this to do whatever you want.

        This override sets the result of this activity to SEARCH_ABORTED and invokes its super method.

      • onCreate

        protected void onCreate(android.os.Bundle savedInstanceState)
        Called when the activity is starting. This is where most initialization should go: calling Activity.setContentView(int) to inflate the activity's UI, using Activity.findViewById(int) to programmatically interact with widgets in the UI, calling Activity.managedQuery(android.net.Uri , String[], String, String[], String) to retrieve cursors for data being displayed, etc.

        You can call Activity.finish(boolean) from within this function, in which case onDestroy() will be immediately called without any of the rest of the activity lifecycle (Activity.onStart(), Activity.onResume(), Activity.onPause(), etc) executing.

        Derived classes must call through to the super class's implementation of this method. If they do not, an exception will be thrown.

        Overrides:
        onCreate in class android.app.Activity
        Parameters:
        savedInstanceState - If the activity is being re-initialized after previously being shut down then this Bundle contains the data it most recently supplied in Activity.onSaveInstanceState(android.os.Bundle). Note: Otherwise it is null.
